        <title>Book Review: Learning PHP, MySQL, and JavaScript: A Step-By-Step Guide to Creating Dynamic Websites (Animal Guide)</title>
        <link>https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/book-review-learning-php-mysql-and-javascript/</link>
        <pubDate>Mon, 17 May 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/book-review-learning-php-mysql-and-javascript/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/book-review-learning-php-mysql-and-javascript/lrg.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Book Review: Learning PHP, MySQL, and JavaScript: A Step-By-Step Guide to Creating Dynamic Websites (Animal Guide)" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; This post was created awhile back on another platform and I migrated to my current one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note I&amp;rsquo;ve matured now and have decided to not post any books I do not like. I apologize in advance for my negative review of this book and I did not intend to be overly negative. I was young and am still learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;learning-php-mysql-and-javascript&#34;&gt;Learning PHP, MySQL, and JavaScript&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;A Step-By-Step Guide to Creating Dynamic Websites (Animal Guide)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0596157134?ie=UTF8&amp;amp;tag=bejeofme-20&amp;amp;linkCode=as2&amp;amp;camp=1789&amp;amp;creative=9325&amp;amp;creativeASIN=0596157134&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgiz-xcT1ve0-7D2WM4lxeQ07NWZ7gAFBfL600uOJ5CKCwGuf7JU4s8-sk0eurZaW820fdq1a_s30_4aQrmW9EntNaSeeD6IBtSEuuCXHT6WDTH73xIjND9bPTP6h5U4iuEK7EooSng2g/s1600/lrg.jpg&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;Book Cover&#34;
	
	
&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;my-review&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;My Review&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I needed to &lt;strong&gt;review PHP&lt;/strong&gt; since many things have changed. I first tried &lt;em&gt;Head First PHP &amp;amp; MySQL&lt;/em&gt;, but it wasn‚Äôt technical enough for me. While I initially thought its teaching style would help, it didn‚Äôt work out.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This book assumes &lt;strong&gt;some programming knowledge&lt;/strong&gt;, which is great because it moves at a faster pace. Unlike &lt;em&gt;Head First PHP &amp;amp; MySQL&lt;/em&gt;, which is slow, this book goes straight to the key subjects‚Äî&lt;strong&gt;PHP, MySQL&lt;/strong&gt;, and even touches on other topics. However, when I reached the &lt;strong&gt;JavaScript section&lt;/strong&gt;, I stopped reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;pros--cons&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pros &amp;amp; Cons&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;-what-i-liked&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‚úÖ What I Liked&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fast-paced&lt;/strong&gt; if you already know some programming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Great MySQL chapters&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì I learned about MySQL database engines like &lt;strong&gt;InnoDB&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;ISAM&lt;/strong&gt; and how to &lt;strong&gt;search databases like a search engine&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Good for PHP basics&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì helped me &lt;strong&gt;dive back into PHP&lt;/strong&gt; and solidify the fundamentals of PHP5.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;-what-i-didnt-like&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‚ùå What I Didn&amp;rsquo;t Like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Too many code errors&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì you can find them listed &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;http://oreilly.com/catalog/errata.csp?isbn=9780596157142&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Confusing examples&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì Some techniques shouldn&amp;rsquo;t even be used in real-world applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PHP authentication example is flawed&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì The book combines &lt;strong&gt;HTTP authentication with PHP sessions&lt;/strong&gt;, but doesn&amp;rsquo;t explain &lt;strong&gt;how to log out properly&lt;/strong&gt;. Deleting browser cookies doesn‚Äôt work, and I had to &lt;strong&gt;Google better solutions&lt;/strong&gt; (hint: use a &lt;strong&gt;logout flag&lt;/strong&gt; in the script).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smarty introduction is weak&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì Installation instructions were unclear, which is why I wrote a &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;http://yourallstar.blogspot.com/2010/05/installation-for-smarty-php-on-wamp.html&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;separate guide&lt;/a&gt; for Windows XP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No Object-Oriented PHP&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì All PHP examples are &lt;strong&gt;procedural&lt;/strong&gt;, with no coverage of &lt;strong&gt;OOP&lt;/strong&gt; in PHP5.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Terrible JavaScript section&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì The JavaScript coding style is &lt;strong&gt;ugly&lt;/strong&gt;, doesn‚Äôt follow &lt;strong&gt;best practices&lt;/strong&gt;, and lacks proper &lt;strong&gt;variable declarations (&lt;code&gt;var variable1&lt;/code&gt;) and semicolons&lt;/strong&gt;. A better &lt;strong&gt;beginner JavaScript book&lt;/strong&gt; would be a wiser choice (I&amp;rsquo;ll post a review of one soon).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;final-verdict&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Final Verdict&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This book is a &lt;strong&gt;basic introduction to PHP&lt;/strong&gt; for those with a programming background. However, it &lt;strong&gt;does not cover Object-Oriented PHP5 at all&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôd rate it &lt;strong&gt;‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è (3/5 stars)&lt;/strong&gt; because it helped me &lt;strong&gt;refresh my PHP knowledge&lt;/strong&gt;, but I &lt;strong&gt;wouldn‚Äôt recommend buying it&lt;/strong&gt;‚Äîespecially if you‚Äôre looking for advanced topics or modern best practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìå &lt;strong&gt;Warning:&lt;/strong&gt; I only read &lt;strong&gt;up to Chapter 16&lt;/strong&gt; (out of 20). I stopped when I reached &lt;strong&gt;JavaScript&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oh, and if you &lt;strong&gt;click the image and buy it from Amazon&lt;/strong&gt;, I get some store credit for more books‚Äîbut honestly, &lt;strong&gt;this isn‚Äôt worth buying&lt;/strong&gt;. üòâ&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>Installation for Smarty PHP on WAMP</title>
        <link>https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/installation-for-smarty-php-on-wamp/</link>
        <pubDate>Fri, 07 May 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/installation-for-smarty-php-on-wamp/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/installation-for-smarty-php-on-wamp/smarty_template_logo.png" alt="Featured image of post Installation for Smarty PHP on WAMP" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; This post was created awhile back on another platform and I migrated to my current one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEgp3eTn3PLLLXEWfJESZe_FpDGOqiGEotuM4pGhCvPniEaB73M6xMjlRsMQYJtfbADoyvJKbzSxP7ugEOxKJu8m-NK2ObVXTTB85ExzEzjwJDuDKpl8EUG_pdolkWetzm85X3XPaWGfPg/s400/smarty-logo-orange.gif&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;Smarty Logo&#34;
	
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I got this from here: &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;http://news.php.net/php.smarty.dev/2703&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;http://news.php.net/php.smarty.dev/2703&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;steps-to-install-smarty&#34;&gt;Steps to Install Smarty:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-download-smartyhttpwwwsmartynetdownloadphp&#34;&gt;1. Download &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;http://www.smarty.net/download.php&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Smarty&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;2-extract-smarty&#34;&gt;2. Extract Smarty&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extract it &lt;strong&gt;outside&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;code&gt;www&lt;/code&gt; folder (e.g., &lt;code&gt;C:\wamp&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;br&gt;
Rename the &lt;code&gt;Smarty.x.x.x&lt;/code&gt; folder to &lt;code&gt;smarty&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;3-edit-phpini&#34;&gt;3. Edit &lt;code&gt;php.ini&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To do this, left-click on the WAMP icon in the system tray, under the &lt;strong&gt;PHP&lt;/strong&gt; menu, there should be a &lt;code&gt;php.ini&lt;/code&gt; option.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example configuration:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ini&#34; data-lang=&#34;ini&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;include_path &lt;span style=&#34;color:#719e07&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;.;C:\wamp\smarty\libs&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WARNING:&lt;/strong&gt; Copy-pasting might create errors with single and double quotes. Make sure to type them manually.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;4-restart-all-services&#34;&gt;4. Restart All Services&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click on the WAMP icon in the system tray and select &lt;strong&gt;Restart All Services&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;5-create-required-folders&#34;&gt;5. Create Required Folders&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your root &lt;code&gt;www&lt;/code&gt; folder, create a directory named &lt;code&gt;smarty&lt;/code&gt;, and within that folder, create:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;templates&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;configs&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Outside of &lt;code&gt;www&lt;/code&gt;, within &lt;code&gt;C:/wamp/smarty&lt;/code&gt;, create:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;templates_c&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;cache&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; There are security concerns for live setups, but for localhost, this is fine. Always use Linux for live testing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;6-create-an-html-file&#34;&gt;6. Create an HTML File&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inside &lt;code&gt;www&lt;/code&gt; or any subfolder within &lt;code&gt;www&lt;/code&gt;, create a file (e.g., &lt;code&gt;index.html&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;7-create-the-template-file&#34;&gt;7. Create the Template File&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create &lt;code&gt;index.tpl&lt;/code&gt; and place it inside &lt;code&gt;www/smarty/templates&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more details, refer to:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;http://news.php.net/php.smarty.dev/2703&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;http://news.php.net/php.smarty.dev/2703&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; Blogspot may parse out HTML tags, so some code might not be displayed correctly.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>Ubercart Quest: Clean URL for Drupal</title>
        <link>https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/ubercart-quest-clean-url-for-drupal/</link>
        <pubDate>Fri, 16 Oct 2009 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/ubercart-quest-clean-url-for-drupal/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://mythicalprogrammer.github.io/p/ubercart-quest-clean-url-for-drupal/ubercart.png" alt="Featured image of post Ubercart Quest: Clean URL for Drupal" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; This post was created awhile back on another platform and I migrated to my current one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;problem&#34;&gt;Problem:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product&amp;rsquo;s images are not showing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One possible cause mentioned in the Ubercart forum is that &lt;strong&gt;Clean URLs&lt;/strong&gt; is not enabled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-1-enable-mod_rewrite&#34;&gt;Step 1: Enable &lt;code&gt;mod_rewrite&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clean URLs requires &lt;code&gt;mod_rewrite&lt;/code&gt; to be enabled&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Note: &lt;code&gt;mod_rewrite&lt;/code&gt; is an Apache 2 module)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To check if &lt;code&gt;mod_rewrite&lt;/code&gt; is enabled, run the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;/usr/sbin/apache2ctl -M
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Look for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rewrite_module
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is the &lt;code&gt;mod_rewrite&lt;/code&gt; module required for Clean URLs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-2-enable-mod_rewrite-if-its-not-enabled&#34;&gt;Step 2: Enable &lt;code&gt;mod_rewrite&lt;/code&gt; if it&amp;rsquo;s not enabled&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To enable &lt;code&gt;mod_rewrite&lt;/code&gt;, run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo /usr/sbin/a2enmod rewrite
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After entering the command, you should see:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Enabling module rewrite.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Run &lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;/etc/init.d/apache2 restart&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; to activate new configuration!
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To disable &lt;code&gt;mod_rewrite&lt;/code&gt;, use:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo /usr/sbin/a2dismod rewrite
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After disabling, you should see:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Module rewrite disabled.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Run &lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;/etc/init.d/apache2 restart&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; to activate new configuration!
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Remember to restart Apache 2 after making changes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-3-check-your-apache-2-configuration&#34;&gt;Step 3: Check Your Apache 2 Configuration&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(I&amp;rsquo;m an Apache 2 noob, so bear with me.)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;code&gt;/etc/apache2/sites-enabled&lt;/code&gt; folder, create a config file for your Drupal site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example file: &lt;code&gt;/etc/apache2/sites-enabled/drupal.conf&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;basic-configuration&#34;&gt;Basic Configuration:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;
&lt;table style=&#34;border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt; 9
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#495050&#34;&gt;10
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-apache&#34; data-lang=&#34;apache&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#268bd2&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;VirtualHost&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;*:80&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#268bd2&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b58900&#34;&gt;ServerName&lt;/span&gt; www.example.com
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#b58900&#34;&gt;DocumentRoot&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;/var/www/drupal-6.13&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#268bd2&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;Directory&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;/var/www/drupal-6.13&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#268bd2&#34;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
